This page documents the item system in Dragon Warrior IV for the NES.

== Overview ==

Dragon Warrior IV uses a single-byte item ID system supporting up to 128 unique items. The item data is distributed across multiple ROM banks, with item names, prices, stats, and equipment restrictions stored in separate tables.

== ROM Data Locations ==

{| class="wikitable"
! Data Type !! ROM Address !! Bank !! Size !! Description
|-
| Item names || $28010 || 20 (PRG $14) || ~$800 || Dictionary-compressed text
|-
| Item prices || $08010 || 4 (PRG $02) || $100 || 2 bytes per item (little-endian)
|-
| Weapon attack || $0a010 || 5 (PRG $02) || $50 || Attack power values
|-
| Armor defense || $0a060 || 5 (PRG $02) || $40 || Defense values
|-
| Equipment flags || $0a100 || 5 (PRG $02) || $80 || Who can equip what
|}

== Item System Overview ==

Items are indexed using 7 bits ($00-$7f). The high bit (bit 7) indicates whether an item is currently equipped. This allows the same byte to store both item identity and equipped status.

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Property !! Value !! Description
|-
| Item ID Range || $00-$7f || 128 possible items
|-
| Equipment Range || $00-$50 || Weapons, armor, shields, helmets
|-
| Consumable Range || $52-$7e || Items used from menu or battle
|-
| Equipped Flag || $80 || Added to ID when item is equipped
|-
| No Item || $7f || Empty slot marker
|-
| Separator || $51 || Blank/unused slot (inventory divider)
|}

